cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the Guruswami-Sudan decoding algorithm for Reed-Solomon codes, which is a topic related to error-correcting codes and information theory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a Divide & Conquer technique to speed up the Kotter-Nielsen-Hoholdt algorithm, which is a well-known algorithm for bivariate interpolation. This is a topic related to data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with polynomial interpolation, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the Kotter-Nielsen-Hoholdt algorithm and proposes a speed-up technique, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The Guruswami-Sudan decoding algorithm is used in control systems and communication networks, which is a topic related to systems and control.
